description: Tottenham have faced Eintracht Frankfurt on six occasions in major European competition, with Feyenoord being the only opponent they’ve faced more often. They have lost just one of the previous six, while they’re unbeaten in the last four – all of which have been since 2022-23. title: PSV Eindhoven vs Bayern Munchen - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD8
description: PSV have only won one of their previous eight meetings with Bayern Munich, with that lone victory coming in a home match back in October 1999 ; goals from Ruud van Nistelrooy and Luc Nilis. PSV have lost more games against Bayern Munich than versus any other opponent in their European competition history. title: Ajax vs Olympiacos - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD8
description: Ajax and Olympiakos have faced each other six times in European competition, with both sides winning two games apiece. This will be the first meeting between Ajax and Olympiakos this century, having last met in the 1998-99 edition of the UEFA Champions League – the Greek side won 1-0 at home in the first game that season, before Ajax won 2-0 in the reverse fixture in Amsterdam.

title: Arsenal vs Kairat Almaty - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD8
description: Arsenal’s meeting with Kairat will be just the second time ever that an English side have hosted an opponent from Kazakhstan in European competition, after Manchester United’s 1-0 win over Astana in September 2019 in the UEFA Europa League.
